User was already there comes by adding devise gem for authontication.

Add association at Users
class User < ActiveRecord::Base  
  has_many :assignments ,:dependent => :destroy
  has_many :roles, :through => :assignments
end

Create role model
rails g model role name:string

Add association at roles
class Role < ActiveRecord::Base

  has_many :assignments,:dependent => :destroy
  has_many :users, :through => :assignments
end

Create assignment model
rails g model assignment

Add following code in migration 
class Assignment < ActiveRecord::belongs
  belongs_to :user
  belongs_to :role
  validates_uniqueness_of :user_id, :scope => :role_id
end

Edit migration file 

class CreateAssignments < ActiveRecord::Migration
def change
    create_table :user_roles do |t|
      t.references :user
      t.references :role	
      t.timestamps
    end
    add_index :assignments, [:user_id, :role_id]
    add_index :assignments, [:role_id, :user_id]
  end
end


At SignUp Form add following checkboxes for role selection.

<p>
    <%= f.label :roles %><br />
    <% for role in Role.all.collect(&:name) %>
      <%= check_box_tag "user[roles][]", role, @user.roles.include?(role) %>
      <%=h role.humanize %><br />
    <% end %>
    <%= hidden_field_tag "user[roles][]", "" %>
  </p>
